sentence: {"text": "The typical Bangladeshi breakfast consists of flour-based flatbreads such as chapati, roti or paratha, served with a curry.", "meaning": "\u5178\u578b\u7684\u5b5f\u52a0\u62c9\u56fd\u65e9\u9910\u5305\u62ec\u9762\u7c89\u7684\u6241\u9762\u5305\uff0c\u5982chapati\uff0croti\u6216paratha\uff0c\u914d\u4e0a\u5496\u55b1\u3002"}
verbs: [{"text": "consists", "tag": "VBZ", "form": "verb, 3rd person singular present", "lemma": "consist"}, {"text": "based", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "base"}, {"text": "served", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "serve"}]

sentence: {"text": "Usually the curry can be vegetable, home-fried potatoes, or scrambled eggs.", "meaning": "\u901a\u5e38\u5496\u55b1\u53ef\u4ee5\u662f\u852c\u83dc\uff0c\u81ea\u5236\u7684\u571f\u8c46\u6216\u7092\u9e21\u86cb\u3002"}
verbs: [{"text": "be", "tag": "VB", "form": "verb, base form", "lemma": "be"}, {"text": "fried", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "fry"}, {"text": "scrambled", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "scramble"}]

sentence: {"text": "The breakfast varies according to location and the eater's income.", "meaning": "\u65e9\u9910\u6839\u636e\u5730\u70b9\u548c\u98df\u8005\u7684\u6536\u5165\u800c\u53d8\u5316\u3002"}
verbs: [{"text": "varies", "tag": "VBZ", "form": "verb, 3rd person singular present", "lemma": "vary"}, {"text": "according", "tag": "VBG", "form": "verb, gerund or present participle", "lemma": "accord"}]

sentence: {"text": "In villages and rural areas, rice with curry (potato mash, dal ) is mostly preferred by day laborers.", "meaning": "\u5728\u6751\u5e84\u548c\u519c\u6751\u5730\u533a\uff0c\u7c73\u996d\u7528\u5496\u55b1\uff08\u9a6c\u94c3\u85af\u6ce5\uff0cDal\uff09\u4e3b\u8981\u662f\u65e5\u5e38\u52b3\u52a8\u8005\u3002"}

{"text": "In the city, sliced bread with jam or jelly is chosen due to time efficiency.", "meaning": "\u5728\u57ce\u5e02\uff0c\u7531\u4e8e\u65f6\u95f4\u6548\u7387\uff0c\u9009\u62e9\u4e86\u679c\u9171\u6216\u679c\u51bb\u7684\u5207\u7247\u9762\u5305\u3002"}
verbs: [{"text": "sliced", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "slice"}, {"text": "is", "tag": "VBZ", "form": "verb, 3rd person singular present", "lemma": "be"}, {"text": "chosen", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "choose"}]

sentence: {"text": "In Bangladesh tea is preferred to coffee and is an essential part of most breakfasts.", "meaning": "\u5728\u5b5f\u52a0\u62c9\u56fd\u8336\u662f\u5496\u5561\uff0c\u662f\u5927\u591a\u6570\u65e9\u9910\u7684\u91cd\u8981\u7ec4\u6210\u90e8\u5206\u3002"}
verbs: [{"text": "is", "tag": "VBZ", "form": "verb, 3rd person singular present", "lemma": "be"}, {"text": "preferred", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "prefer"}, {"text": "is", "tag": "VBZ", "form": "verb, 3rd person singular present", "lemma": "be"}]

sentence: {"text": "Having toasted biscuits, bread or puffed rice with tea is also very popular.", "meaning": "\u559d\u70e4\u997c\u5e72\uff0c\u9762\u5305\u6216\u81a8\u5316\u7c73\u996d\u4e5f\u5f88\u53d7\u6b22\u8fce\u3002"}
verbs: [{"text": "Having", "tag": "VBG", "form": "verb, gerund or present participle", "lemma": "have"}, {"text": "toasted", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "toast"}, {"text": "puffed", "tag": "VBN", "form": "verb, past participle", "lemma": "puff"}, {"text": "is", "tag": "VBZ", "form": "verb, 3rd person singular present", "lemma": "be"}]
